Preconditions:
The input parameter `customers` is a 2D array of integers representing the arrival time and the duration of each customer's service.
The `customers` array is not null.
The `customers` array has at least one row.

Postconditions:
The method returns a double value representing the average waiting time of all customers.
The returned average waiting time is accurate within a tolerance of `10^-5` from the actual answer.